{"id":"captive","term":"Captive","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>One taken in war. Captives were often treated with great cruelty and indignity (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 20:32\">1 Kings 20:32</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 10:24\">Josh. 10:24</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Judges 1:7\">Judg. 1:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 4:12\">2 Sam. 4:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Judges 8:7\">Judg. 8:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 12:31\">2 Sam. 12:31</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 20:3\">1 Chr. 20:3</a>). When a city was taken by assault, all the men were slain, and the women and children carried away captive and sold as slaves (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 20:1\">Isa. 20</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 47:3\">47:3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 28:9\">2 Chr. 28:9-15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 44:12\">Ps. 44:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joel 3:3\">Joel 3:3</a>), and exposed to the most cruel treatment (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nahum 3:10\">Nah. 3:10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Zechariah 14:2\">Zech. 14:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Esther 3:13\">Esther 3:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 8:12\">2 Kings 8:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 13:16\">Isa. 13:16</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 13:18\">18</a>). Captives were sometimes carried away into foreign countries, as was the case with the Jews (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 20:5\">Jer. 20:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 39:9\">39:9</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 39:10\">10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 40:7\">40:7</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Kings 20:32","Joshua 10:24","Judges 1:7","2 Samuel 4:12","Judges 8:7","2 Samuel 12:31","1 Chronicles 20:3","Isaiah 20:1","Isaiah 47:3","2 Chronicles 28:9","Psalms 44:12","Joel 3:3","Nahum 3:10","Zechariah 14:2","Esther 3:13","2 Kings 8:12","Isaiah 13:16","Isaiah 13:18","Jeremiah 20:5","Jeremiah 39:9","Jeremiah 39:10","Jeremiah 40:7"]}